                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1165" type="given" value="WALTER"></interp>WALTER CROW</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of Mr. Charles Coley, pawnbroker. Norfolk-street, Islington. These trowsers are his property—I saw them safe between three and four o'clock on the afternoon of the 25th of February—the policeman brought them between five and six o'clock.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183702270175"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> They are my own. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> No, they are my matter's—they were marked on each side, and the mark it torn off—I swear to them from having no lining and by the shape of them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370227-name-1166" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1166" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
