                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1166" type="given" value="THOMAS HOBBS"></interp>THOMAS HOBBS KING</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 248.) I taw the prisoner in the Lower-road about four o'clock, about one hundred and fifty yards from the prosecutor's shop—there was a man and two women with him—I ran and took one of the men—I saw the prisoner again a little after five o'clock—I took him with these trowsers, and took the shoes out of his pocket.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I am a general dealer. I bought these trowsers in Cutler-street, Houndsditch.</p>
